issue.title: Fix logout to route back to home page
issue.body: After logout, the profile page does not switch back to the home page.

issue.title: Create 'authorize newly registered users' page (admin side)
issue.body:
Implement the 'authorized newly registered user' page.

This page should:
- List all the accounts that have been registered but not yet approved.
- Allow the admin to see all the registration details.
- Check a box and press submit to authorize the registration.
- Check a box to indicate if a text message notification should be sent.
- Upon authorization, the system should send a text message indicating the registration has been authorized to the user if the associated box is checked.

issue.title: Create admin home page (admin side)
issue.body:
- Create the home page for administrators (depends on issue 1)
- Provide menu items to additional admin pages:
  - Authorize new registered users.
  - Schedule visitation.
  - Send text reminder.

issue.title: Fix the update profile info page
issue.body:
Visitors should be able to:
1. Sign up using email and a password
2. Prompt user to update info before requesting a visit
3. Update Users database with profile info from contact-information page

issue.title: Create 'request visit' page (visitor side)
issue.body:
After a visitor's registration has been approved by OCCC staff, their home page should display the 'request visit' page when they do not have a currently scheduled visit. 

This page should:
- Display some potential visitation dates in the next seven days.
- Enable the visitor to check the date they are interested in.
- Submit the request for admin review.

issue.title: Create 'cancel visit' page (visitor side)
issue.body:
When a visitor has a scheduled visit, upon logging in they should see the 'scheduled visit' page.

This page should:
- Provides the date and time of their scheduled visit.
- Documentation on the dress code and document requirements.
- A button that allows them to cancel the visit request.

If they cancel the visit, then after that the visitor home page should show the 'request visit' page.

issue.title: Create 'pending authorization' page (visitor side)
issue.body:
When a visitor has registered with the system but is not yet authorized by an admin, then their home page should simply indicate:
- The time and date that they registered.
- That their registration request is under review by OCCC staff.

issue.title: Create 'pending visit request' page (visitor side)
issue.body:
When a visitor has requested a visit but it has not yet been approved by OCCC staff, upon logging in their home page should display the 'pending visit request' page.

This page should:
- Display the requested visit time and date.
- Inform the visitor that their request is under review.
- Allow the visitor to cancel the request.

If they cancel the request, then after that they go to the 'schedule visit request' page.

issue.title: Create 'cancel visits' page (admin side)
issue.body:
Create a page that enables OCCC staff to cancel scheduled visits (due to staff shortage or whatever).

This page should:
- List all scheduled visits for the next seven days.
- Provide a checkbox next to each visit to indicate if it should be canceled.
- For each visit, also provide a checkbox indicating if a text message notification should be sent.
- Provide a text field that OCCC staff can use to describe why the visit is being cancelled.
- Upon submission, the scheduled visits are removed, and text messages indicating that along with the explanation are sent out.
